cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The problem involves wires and tangles, which are concepts commonly studied in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of multiset of swaps and the aim to find a tangle that realizes the swaps with the smallest number of layers suggest that the problem may also be related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The fact that the problem is NP-hard and involves combinatorial optimization suggests that it may also be related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
